+{"id":"frankenredis-7rp6","title":"[HIGH] TTL accounting diverges from Redis for absolute-time expiry (EXPIREAT/PEXPIREAT/SET EXAT/SET PXAT/GETEX EXAT/PXAT/PERSIST)","description":"Surfaced by live_redis_core_strings_matches_runtime: ~10 cases where ours returns stale fake-clock-driven residuals instead of upstream's -2 / nil for keys whose absolute-time deadline is in the past relative to wall clock. Cases: pexpiretime_abskey, expiretime_abskey, pttl_whenkey_after_expireat, pexpireat_whenkey, pttl_whenkey_after_pexpireat, expiretime_whenkey, getex_verify_ttl_after_exat, getex_with_pxat, getex_verify_pttl_after_pxat, getex_with_persist, getex_verify_ttl_after_persist, set_exat_verify_ttl, set_pxat_verify_pttl. Root cause likely: harness now_ms fixture clock vs real absolute-time comparison in Store::evaluate_expiry. Fix in fr-store expiry path or fixture scheduling.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T04:07:16.201304326Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T04:07:16.201304326Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-t3xa","title":"[HIGH] Error wording: SETEX/PSETEX zero/negative reports 'not an integer or out of range' instead of 'invalid expire time'","description":"Surfaced by live_redis_core_strings_matches_runtime: 3 cases — setex_zero_error, psetex_zero_ms_error, psetex_negative_ms_error. Upstream: 'ERR invalid expire time in <cmd>'. Ours: 'ERR value is not an integer or out of range'. Fix: in fr-command SET/SETEX/PSETEX parser, preserve the integer parse but validate the seconds/ms > 0 with the upstream wording.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T04:07:16.301214993Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T04:07:16.301214993Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-68ql","title":"[HIGH] LCS/SUBSTR/SETRANGE error-wording divergences (WRONGTYPE vs ERR, substr vs getrange, proto-max-bulk-len)","description":"Surfaced by live_redis_core_strings_matches_runtime: lcs_wrongtype (WRONGTYPE vs 'ERR The specified keys must contain string values'), lcs_len_only_ignores_idx (we return integer, upstream rejects), lcs_minmatchlen_negative (upstream accepts, we reject as syntax), substr_wrong_arity (command name leaks 'getrange'), setrange_huge_offset ('512MB' vs 'proto-max-bulk-len'). Fix in fr-command LCS/SUBSTR/SETRANGE paths.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T04:07:16.389207303Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T04:07:16.389207303Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-a118","title":"[HIGH] HINCRBYFLOAT Infinity error wording + HRANDFIELD arity error drift","description":"Surfaced by live_redis_core_hash_matches_runtime: 5 HINCRBYFLOAT inf/-inf/inf-minus-inf cases emit 'ERR increment would produce NaN or Infinity' where upstream emits 'ERR value is NaN or Infinity'. Plus hrandfield_too_many_args returns 'ERR wrong number of arguments' where upstream returns 'ERR syntax error'. Fix in fr-command HINCRBYFLOAT + HRANDFIELD.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T04:07:16.476781813Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T04:07:16.476781813Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-zk9q","title":"[HIGH] HGETALL field iteration order differs from upstream (fixture captures upstream ordering)","description":"Surfaced by live_redis_core_hash_matches_runtime case hgetall_result: upstream returns [name,alice,age,30] (insertion order), ours returns [age,30,name,alice]. HGETALL order is technically unspecified in Redis, but the fixture was captured from upstream. Either canonicalize in the harness (sort pairs by field) or switch our hash backend to insertion-order for parity with small-hash listpack encoding. Fix in fr-store Hash::entries iteration or conformance harness comparator.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T04:07:16.565993252Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T04:07:16.565993252Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
